Citation.sTitle: Measurement and Correlation of the Solubilities of Oxygen, Nitrogen, and Carbon Dioxide in JP-10
Citation.sAbstract: New experimental solubility data of nitrogen, oxygen, and carbon dioxide in JP-10 (exo-tetrahydrodicyclopentadiene) in the temperature range from 293K to 343K in the intervals of 10 K and in the pressure range from 0.5 MPa to 7.5 MPa were reported. The relative expanded uncertainty of solubility measurement is estimated to be less than 4 % with a level of confidence of 95 %. The solubility order of the three gases in JP-10 in the studied temperature and pressure range is: carbon dioxide greater than oxygen greater than nitrogen. The Henry s constants and the thermodynamic properties of solvation were calculated from the solubility data. A modified KK equation was used to represent the experimental data with AARD less than 1.9 %.
